<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Fourth Book of Moses, called Numbers, Chapter 31 - Sacred Name 
King James Version</TITLE><link rel=stylesheet href=style1.css type=text/css>   
</HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James    
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B04C030.htm'>Numbers 30</A></P><CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
The Fourth Book of Moses, called Numbers</H2></CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>   
Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD>
</TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 31</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH spake unto Moses, saying,</P></TD></TR>  
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Avenge the children of      
Israel of the Midianites: afterward shalt thou be gathered unto thy people.</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses spake   
unto the people, saying, Arm some of yourselves unto the war, and let them go   
against the Midianites, and avenge YHVH of Midian.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD         
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>Of every tribe a thousand,          
throughout all the tribes of Israel, shall ye send to the war.</P></TD></TR><TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>So there were delivered out of  
the thousands of Israel, a thousand of every tribe, twelve thousand armed for   
war.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses 
sent them to the war, a thousand of every tribe, them and Phinehas the son of   
Eleazar the priest, to the war, with the holy instruments, and the trumpets to  
blow in his hand.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD>
<P>And they warred against the Midianites, as YHVH commanded Moses; and they    
slew all the males.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD>  
<TD><P>And they slew the kings of Midian, beside the rest of them that were     
slain; namely, Evi, and Rekem, and Zur, and Hur, and Reba, five kings of        
Midian: Balaam also the son of Beor they slew with the sword.</P></TD></TR><TR> 
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>And the children of Israel took 
all the women of Midian captives, and their little ones, and took the spoil of  
all their cattle, and all their flocks, and all their goods.</P></TD></TR><TR>  
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>And they burnt all their      
cities wherein they dwelt, and all their goodly castles, with fire.</P></TD>    
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>And they took all    
the spoil, and all the prey, both of men and of beasts.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD    
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>And they brought the captives,    
and the prey, and the spoil, unto Moses, and Eleazar the priest, and unto the   
congregation of the children of Israel, unto the camp at the plains of Moab,    
which are by Jordan near Jericho.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13>  
<H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses, and Eleazar the priest, and all the princes   
of the congregation, went forth to meet them without the camp.</P></TD></TR><TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses was wroth with the  
officers of the host, with the captains over thousands, and captains over       
hundreds, which came from the battle.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses said unto them, Have ye saved all the 
women alive?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>
Behold, these caused the children of Israel, through the counsel of Balaam, to  
commit trespass against YHVH in the matter of Peor, and there was a plague      
among the congregation of YHVH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>
17</H4></TD><TD><P>Now therefore kill every male among the little ones, and     
kill every woman that hath known man by lying with him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD    
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>But all the women children, that  
have not known a man by lying with him, keep alive for yourselves.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>And do ye abide without   
the camp seven days: whosoever hath killed any person, and whosoever hath       
touched any slain, purify both yourselves and your captives on the third day,   
and on the seventh day.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4> 
</TD><TD><P>And purify all your raiment, and all that is made of skins, and all 
work of goats' hair, and all things made of wood.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD          
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>And Eleazar the priest said unto  
the men of war which went to the battle, This is the ordinance of the law which 
YHVH commanded Moses;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4>   
</TD><TD><P>Only the gold, and the silver, the brass, the iron, the tin, and    
the lead,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD><TD><P>   
Every thing that may abide the fire, ye shall make it go through the fire, and  
it shall be clean: nevertheless it shall be purified with the water of          
separation: and all that abideth not the fire ye shall make go through the      
water.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD><TD><P>And   
ye shall wash your clothes on the seventh day, and ye shall be clean, and       
afterward ye shall come into the camp.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V25><H4>25</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH spake unto Moses, saying,</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V26><H4>26</H4></TD><TD><P>Take the sum of the prey  
that was taken, both of man and of beast, thou, and Eleazar the priest, and the 
chief fathers of the congregation:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V27> 
<H4>27</H4></TD><TD><P>And divide the prey into two parts; between them that    
took the war upon them, who went out to battle, and between all the             
congregation:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V28><H4>28</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>And levy a tribute unto YHVH of the men of war which went out to battle: one 
soul of five hundred, both of the persons, and of the beeves, and of the asses, 
and of the sheep:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V29><H4>29</H4></TD>  
<TD><P>Take it of their half, and give it unto Eleazar the priest, for an heave 
offering of YHVH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V30><H4>30</H4></TD>  
<TD><P>And of the children of Israel's half, thou shalt take one portion of     
fifty, of the persons, of the beeves, of the asses, and of the flocks, of all   
manner of beasts, and give them unto the Levites, which keep the charge of the  
tabernacle of YHVH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V31><H4>31</H4></TD>
<TD><P>And Moses and Eleazar the priest did as YHVH commanded Moses.</P></TD>   
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V32><H4>32</H4></TD><TD><P>And the booty, being 
the rest of the prey which the men of war had caught, was six hundred thousand  
and seventy thousand and five thousand sheep,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>  
<A NAME=V33><H4>33</H4></TD><TD><P>And threescore and twelve thousand           
beeves,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V34><H4>34</H4></TD><TD><P>And  
threescore and one thousand asses,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V35> 
<H4>35</H4></TD><TD><P>And thirty and two thousand persons in all, of women     
that had not known man by lying with him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V36><H4>36</H4></TD><TD><P>And the half, which was the portion of them     
that went out to war, was in number three hundred thousand and seven and thirty 
thousand and five hundred sheep:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V37>   
<H4>37</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH's tribute of the sheep was six hundred and      
threescore and fifteen.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V38><H4>38</H4> 
</TD><TD><P>And the beeves were thirty and six thousand; of which YHVH's        
tribute was threescore and twelve.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V39> 
<H4>39</H4></TD><TD><P>And the asses were thirty thousand and five hundred; of  
which YHVH's tribute was threescore and one.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V40><H4>40</H4></TD><TD><P>And the persons were sixteen thousand; of which 
YHVH's tribute was thirty and two persons.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V41><H4>41</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses gave the tribute, which was YHVH's    
heave offering, unto Eleazar the priest, as YHVH commanded Moses.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V42><H4>42</H4></TD><TD><P>And of the children of    
Israel's half, which Moses divided from the men that warred,</P></TD></TR><TR>  
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V43><H4>43</H4></TD><TD><P>(Now the half that pertained  
unto the congregation was three hundred thousand and thirty thousand and seven  
thousand and five hundred sheep,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V44>   
<H4>44</H4></TD><TD><P>And thirty and six thousand beeves,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V45><H4>45</H4></TD><TD><P>And thirty thousand asses and     
five hundred,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V46><H4>46</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>And sixteen thousand persons;)</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V47>  
<H4>47</H4></TD><TD><P>Even of the children of Israel's half, Moses took one    
portion of fifty, both of man and of beast, and gave them unto the Levites,     
which kept the charge of the tabernacle of YHVH; as YHVH commanded Moses.</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V48><H4>48</H4></TD><TD><P>And the         
officers which were over thousands of the host, the captains of thousands, and  
captains of hundreds, came near unto Moses:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V49><H4>49</H4></TD><TD><P>And they said unto Moses, Thy servants have     
taken the sum of the men of war which are under our charge, and there lacketh   
not one man of us.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V50><H4>50</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>We have therefore brought an oblation for YHVH, what every man hath      
gotten, of jewels of gold, chains, and bracelets, rings, earrings, and tablets, 
to make an atonement for our souls before YHVH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>
<A NAME=V51><H4>51</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses and Eleazar the priest took the    
gold of them, even all wrought jewels.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V52><H4>52</H4></TD><TD><P>And all the gold of the offering that they      
offered up to YHVH, of the captains of thousands, and of the captains of        
hundreds, was sixteen thousand seven hundred and fifty shekels.</P></TD></TR>   
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V53><H4>53</H4></TD><TD><P>(For the men of war had   
taken spoil, every man for himself.)</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A         
NAME=V54><H4>54</H4></TD><TD><P>And Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold  
of the captains of thousands and of hundreds, and brought it into the           
tabernacle of the congregation, for a memorial for the children of Israel       
before YHVH.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by John   
